    <div class="main-information">
      <h1>Sports Physiotherapy</h1>
      <img src="images/ourServicesData/specialisedData/sports (2).jpg" loading="lazy" alt="Sports Therapy" />
      <p>
        Sports Physiotherapy is a specialized branch of Physiotherapy which deals
        with the problems related to injuries that mainly occur during a sports
        event or after that (whether it is on-filed or off-field.)
      </p>
      <p>
        Sports therapists play a huge role in helping out sportspersons of all
        ages and at different sports levels to enhance their ability to perform
        well. They have a role in pre-participation evaluation, the decision of
        clearance to play, and planning the rest & recovery schedule of athletes.
      </p>
      <p>Sports physiotherapists also work and travel with individual players or teams, coordinate with other medical
        professionals, and helps in training, injury prevention, rehabilitation, and promote health and skill related
        components of player/athlete. (like strength, endurance, coordination, reaction time, balance, power, etc.)</p>
      <p>Performance enhancement is one of the major goals of sports physiotherapy. Thus, it has become an integral part
        of any sport in today&apos;s era.</p>
    </div>
