    <div class="information-3">
      <h5>
        How our Sports Physiotherapists (SP) works?
      </h5>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Sports therapist assess their athletes in a proper manner and also train them according to their sports.
        </li>
        <li>
          Our SP provides training sessions along with proper warm-ups and cool down in order to enhance performance and
          decrease the chances of injuries during any sports.
        </li>
        <li>
          SP helps by giving advice related to play techniques and proper equipment to the athletes which help in
          preventing injuries.
        </li>
        <li>SP train the athletes in a manner so that they can perform their best during the competition without any
          chances of getting injured.
        </li>
        <li> Twisting injuries</li>
        <li> Ankle Sprains</li>
        <li>Strains</li>
        <li> SP plan the post-injury rehab program for the athletes which helps them to return to their game again with
          full confidence, restored functions, and without any pain or inability.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="information-with-point-2">
      <div class="information-2-image">
        <img src="images/ourServicesData/specialisedData/sports-2.jpg" loading="lazy" alt="Sports Therapy" />
      </div>
      <div class="information-2">
        <ul>
          <li>
            Along with injury treatment, SP also works in the field for proper assessment as well as training for a
            specific event or in other words training of specific movement or muscles that are used during sports
            activity so as to prevent it from any injury.
          </li>
          <li>
            Sports Physiotherapy helps in providing a good rehab program in order to help an athlete return to their
            sports after the injury.
          </li>
          <li>
            The instant when a player gets injured in the field it&apos;s the duty of Sports therapists who have to work
            and decide the most appropriate treatment they can provide in order to help their players get back to their
            game. It&apos;s the Sports therapist who decides whether the player is fit for the event or not.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
